Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy
Magimix UK Limited (“Magimix” / “we” / “our” / “us”) is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. We collect and process your personal data in compliance with applicable data protection laws, including the UK Data Protection Act 2018 and General Data Protection Regulation.
This Privacy Policy sets out the basis on which we will process your personal information when you use our website,
https://www.magimix.co.uk
(which we refer to as the “Magimix Website”), or otherwise in connection with the sale of our products. It only applies if you are in the UK, and does not apply to your use of any other Magimix website.
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand what data we collect about you, how and why we process that data, and your rights and choices relating to that data.
1- WHO WE ARE
Magimix UK Limited is a company registered in England and Wales under company number 02142370. Our registered office is at 19 Bridge Street, Godalming, Surrey, GU7 1HY, England.  We are part of a group of companies with MAGIMIX France, whose head office is 48 rue des Vignerons 94300 Vincennes and registered with RCS Créteil 379 216 112, SAS with a capital of 40 000€.
The Magimix Website is owned and operated by MAGIMIX France.
2- WHEN DO WE COLLECT PERSONAL DATA?
We collect personal data from you when you submit information directly to us or via the Magimix Website. You will be required to give us personal data when you:
- create your account
- log in to your account
- order and pay for products
- register your products (e.g. for a warranty)
- find your nearest stockist (using your location)
- request to be notified when an item is back in stock
- save your basket
- cancel your order or end your contract with us
- return any products
- participate in a quiz / complete a feedback form
- leave a comment or review on a product
- leave a comment or review on a recipe
- submit a recipe
- sign up for or give consent to receive our newsletter and/or promotional offers
- contact or correspond with us for any other reason
Certain personal data which we ask you to provide in the order process is mandatory; this is indicated by a red asterisk or triangle on the Magimix Website. All other data we ask you to provide is optional.
In addition to the information you give to us, we will collect certain information when you visit and use the Magimix Website (see WHAT TYPES OF PERSONAL DATA DO WE COLLECT? below).
3- WHAT TYPES OF PERSONAL DATA DO WE COLLECT?
We collect the following data:
Contact details and account information:
- country of residence, first name, surname and date of birth
- email address
- hone number
- account password (if applicable)
Order details:
- delivery information, including delivery address and delivery method
- order history, including details of product(s) purchased, date of purchase and proof of purchase
Connection data and cookies:
- certain technical information, including type of device, IP address, browser type and version
- information about your visit to, and device interaction with, the Magimix Website (such as scrolling and clicks)
- certain cookies or other tracking technologies
Location data:
- geographical position
Other information:
- preferences (including whether you wish to receive newsletters and/or promotional offers)
- comments, ratings and reviews
- recipe submissions, comments on recipes, and favourite recipes
- information in any correspondence with us
We may also collect anonymous data (or anonymise personal data that we collect from you). This means it is not possible to identify who that data is connected to. We may use this data without any further permission from you.
4- WHY DO WE COLLECT YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
We will only process your personal data for the following reasons:
- to enable us to fulfil the contractual commitments in our contract with you
- to enable us to pursue our legitimate interest in providing and improving our products and services
- to comply with applicable laws
- if you have given us your consent (this only applies in limited circumstances - see below)
Where we need consent to process your personal data (for example, in order to send you newsletters or promotional offers), we will ask you to positively opt-in by ticking the appropriate consent box on the Magimix Website.
